<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>PCCurrency</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <a href="/">Return to PCCurrency</a>
        <h1>Mining difficulty</h1>
        PCCurrency is not a cryptocurrency, but it has "mining" feature that lets you push on your computer to earn PCCurrency.
        <br>
        The target hash must start with some amount of zeros. This is the difficulty.
        <br>
        The difficulty can't be less than 1 and more than 32.
        <br>
        <form action="/difficulty">
            Target hash must start with <input name="difficulty" type="number" value="<nodejs-embed>currentDifficulty</nodejs-embed>"></input> zeros. <br>
            <button>Apply and return to PCCurrency</button>
        </form>
    </body>
</html>